      "writtenOn": "2020-04-11T22:14:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I updated the commit message. Does this match your expectations?\n\n\nPreferences are a tricky thing 😊\n\nI agree that the commit hash is more valuable than the date. Personally, I\u0027d like the date *in addition* to the hash, to get a quick idea of the roll\u0027s time span. At the same time, I\u0027d prefer to skip the list altogether, and replace it with a URL to a UI that lets me browse the log.\n\n* gitiles example: https://chromium.googlesource.com/external/github.com/google/googletest/+log/eb78ee170..e3f0319d8\n* github example: https://github.com/google/googletest/compare/eb78ee170...e3f0319d8\n\nI only brought up my personal preferences to make the point that \npreferences are tricky 😊 I\u0027m happy to abdicate preferences in return for being able to use the same script to roll deps in all our repositories 😊\n\nI\u0027ll try to put together a CL for depot_tools. If it takes less than an hour to do that, I think it\u0027s the easiest way to kick off the conversation.",
